From: =?utf-8?q?Jos=C3=A9_Padilla?= <jpadilla@webapplicate.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 2026 12:46:08 -0400
Subject: Merge commit from fork

Co-authored-by: José Padilla <jpadilla@users.noreply.github.com>

Origin: backport, https://github.com/jpadilla/pyjwt/commit/051ea341b5573fe3edcd53042f347929b92c2b92

The Debian python3-jwt 1.7.1-2+deb11u1 source package ships this
backport written in Python 3-only syntax (typing imports, PEP 526
variable annotations, function annotations, the keyword-only `*`
marker, `set[str]` / `dict[str, Any]` generics, f-strings) because
Debian only builds python3-jwt for bullseye-security and there is no
python-jwt (py2) package to keep compatible. PyJWT 1.7.1 itself is
still py2-compatible, and SlapOS uses 1.7.1 as the py2 PyJWT, so the
api_jws.py hunks have been rewritten with only constructs that exist
in Python 2.7 (frozenset literal, positional/default args,
%-formatting, isinstance against the already-imported `string_types`).
The semantics of the backport are preserved: tokens with an
unsupported / malformed `crit` header are rejected with the same
exception type and message families.
